[Canine distemper virus is probably the pathogen that has the greatest impact on wild carnivore populations at the domestic-wildlife interface. Epidemic events originating in domestic dogs have been well studied and documented in several wild carnivore species. It is very important to make sure to keep the vaccination schemes of all dogs in the area up to date.

For a video of a raccoon with distemper go to
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H22KFjDnY08&feature=related.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the affected area can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1_Rb. - Mod.PMB]
